The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 January is 178,440 (20,566.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 January, there were 7,726 new confirmed cases (890.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 January, there were 9,755 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (2,029 fewer cases).
